    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-08-04T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-08-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="196"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d196">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Roosevelt Papers: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Prime Minister <persName type="from">Churchill</persName> to
                        President <persName type="to">Roosevelt</persName>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d196fn1">Channel of transmission to Washington not
                        indicated. Forwarded by the <gloss target="#t_White1">White</gloss> House
                        Map Room to Roosevelt, who was then at Birch Island, as telegram No. <gloss
                            target="#t_White1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">White</hi>
                        </gloss> 42.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">most secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-08-04">4 August
                            1943</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_FNP1">Former Naval Person</gloss> to President. Personal and
                    most secret. Nr. 404.</p>
                <p>Reference your telegram nr. 340.<note n="2" xml:id="d196fn2">
                        <hi rend="italic">Supra</hi>.</note> On suggestion of Mr. Mackenzie King
                    words “later on” will be substituted for “thereafter” in last sentence of
                    proposed announcement and latter will not be issued until after arrival at
                        <gloss target="#t_Abraham1">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Abraham</hi>
                    </gloss>.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
